When you have internal user directory and "higher" directories listed above it, user browser only lists groups from topmost-matched directory for a user that exists in multiple directories. However the remote API returns all users from all directories regardless their order when you fetch a group and list its members.

Directory1 (with local groups): GroupA: { mdoe }
Internal: GroupA { jdoe, mdoe }

If Directory 1 is the topmost directory in settings page getGroup(session, "GroupA") will return remoteGroup with members jdoe and mdoe. This makes it impossible to assign user to group "GroupA" in "AD directory with local groups" when internal directory contains same-named user. Workaround is to disable Directory1, remove all group memberships with remote calls and then enable Directory1 and assign groups then.

I'm unsure whether this is a bug or a feature...

