By default JIRA is installed as service on Windows. Since Windows doesn't allow a user to access another user's process, logon user can't access JIRA process.

!StackTrace.png!

Documentation doesn't provide steps needed to workaround this problem. Also StackTrace tool won't be able to access 32 bit process if run by 64 bit Java.
